[[Image:Sultan Omar Ali Saifuddien Mosque; 2002.jpg|thumb|200px|left|The Great Mosque in Brunei]] {{islam by country}}
[[Islam]] is [[Brunei]]'s official religion, 82.70 percent of the population is Muslim,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/bx.html#People|title=The World Factbook — Central Intelligence Agency|author=|date=|website=www.cia.gov|accessdate=21 April 2018}}</ref> mostly [[Sunni]]s of [[Malay people|Malay]] origin who follow the [[Shafi]] school of Islamic law. Most of the other Muslim groups are Malay Brunei, Malay [[Kedayan]]s (converts from indigenous tribal groups) and Chinese converts.<ref>Islamic banking in Southeast Asia, Islam in Brunei pushes other religions out of the way . E.g. The ban on alcohol, The ban on the teachings of other religions etc. This is often widely criticised, The Government always attempts to hide this. By Mohamed Ariff, Institute of Southeast Asian Studies, pg. 24</ref>
==History== Islam was adopted in the 15th century when a Malay Muslim was installed as [[sultan]]. The sultan traditionally was responsible for upholding Islamic traditions, although the responsibility was usually delegated to appointed officials.
Since the 1930s sultans have used rising oil revenues to provide an extensive social welfare system and promote Islam, including subsidizing the [[Hajj]], building [[mosque]]s, and expanding the Department of Religious Affairs.
With the constitution in 1959, Islam became the official religion of the country.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bt.com.bn/art-culture/2010/03/08/golden-history-islam-brunei |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-10-02 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151003072346/http://www.bt.com.bn/art-culture/2010/03/08/golden-history-islam-brunei |archivedate=2015-10-03 |df= }}</ref>
On 30 April 2014, [[List of Sultans of Brunei|Sultan]] [[Hassanal Bolkiah]] announced the implementation and enforcement of the first phase of [[Sharia]] law in Brunei starting 1 May 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/apr/30/sultan-brunei-sharia-penal-code-flogging-death-stoning|title=Sultan of Brunei unveils strict sharia penal code|first=Agence France-Presse in|last=Brunei|date=30 April 2014|website=the Guardian|accessdate=21 April 2018}}</ref>
