{{Infobox organization | name = Pakistan Sikh Gurdwara Prabandhak Committee | native_name = ਪਾਕਿਸਤਾਨ ਸਿੱਖ ਗੁਰਦੁਆਰਾ ਪ੍ਰਬੰਧਕ ਕਮੇਟੀ | abbreviation = | image = File:Gurdwara Dera Sahib Panjvin Patshahi.jpg | image_size = 200px | caption= Gurdwara Dera Sahib Panjvin Patshahi, PSGPC Headquarters | type = Constitutional Body | status = Active | formation = | founder = [[Evacuee Trust Property Board]] | headquarters = [[Gurdwara Dera Sahib]], [[Lahore]], [[Punjab, Pakistan]] | coordinates = | origins = | key_people = | region_served = [[Pakistan]] | language = [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]] | leader_title = President | leader_name = | main_organ = | mission = | purpose = Management of Sikh [[Gurdwara]]s in [[Pakistan]] | method = | affiliations = [[Evacuee Trust Property Board]] | slogan = | volunteers = | membership = | former name = Evacuee Trust Property Board | homepage = {{URL|http://www.etpb.gov.pk/psgpc.html}} | footnotes = }} {{Sikhism sidebar}} {{portal|Sikhism}}
The '''Pakistan Sikh Gurdwara Prabandhak Committee''' (or '''PSGPC''') is a [[Sikh]] religious organisation in [[Pakistan]].<ref name="PTI 2016">{{cite web | author=PTI | title=Pakistan Sikh body elects caretaker president | website=The Hindu | date=1 April 2016 | url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/international/pakistan-sikh-body-elects-caretaker-president/article8423115.ece | accessdate=20 April 2016}}</ref><ref name="Service 2016">{{cite web | last=Service | first=Tribune News | title=Pak Sikhs leaving abroad must inform PSGPC | website=tribuneindia.com| date=20 April 2016 | url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/news/world/pak-sikhs-leaving-abroad-must-inform-psgpc/117070.html | accessdate=20 April 2016}}</ref> PSGPC was formed by the [[Government of Pakistan]] and is entrusted with the maintenance of Sikh religious institutions, places of worships in Pakistan. Unlike [[Shiromani Gurdwara Prabandhak Committee]] (SGPC) in [[India]], PSGPC is not an Independent fully Sikh-owned body and is controlled by Evacuee Trust Property Board (ETPB) of Pakistan.<ref name="Rana 2014">{{cite web | last=Rana | first=Yudhvir | title=Calendar: Makkar returns without any assurance from PSGPC | website=The Times of India | date=23 May 2014 | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Calendar-Makkar-returns-without-any-assurance-from-PSGPC/articleshow/35490430.cms | accessdate=20 April 2016}}</ref><ref name="Rana 2015">{{cite web | last=Rana | first=Yudhvir | title=DSGMC calls upon Pak Sikhs to initiate movement to bring Gurdwara's out of control of ET PB | website=The Times of India | date=3 July 2015 | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/DSGMC-calls-upon-Pak-Sikhs-to-initiate-movement-to-bring-Gurdwaras-out-of-control-of-ET-PB/articleshow/47927955.cms | accessdate=20 April 2016}}</ref> This organisation is entrusted with the maintenance of Sikh religious institutions, places of worships (''[[gurdwara]]'') and the well-being of the Pakistani Sikh community.<ref name="ETPB">{{cite web | title=Evacuee Trust Property Board Shrine Branch | website=ETPB | url=http://www.etpb.gov.pk/shrinebranch.html | accessdate=20 April 2016}}</ref> Its main organisation is based in [[Lahore]] in the province of [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]]. However, the PSGPC is opposed by the SGPC, which regards itself as the sole guardian of Sikh institutions and religion worldwide. The right to sole guardian is given to SGPC every 4 years in a fair elections in which sikhs from around the world participate. SGPC was created in 1920s.
