[[File:The Iowa Jewish News cover.jpg|thumb|Cover of ''The Iowa Jewish News'']]'''''The Iowa Jewish News''''' was a Jewish weekly newspaper published from [[Des Moines]], [[Iowa]], the [[United States]] 1932-1952.<ref name="Drachler1996">{{cite book|author=Norman Drachler|title=A Bibliography of Jewish Education in the United States|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=74WxERjUz0IC&pg=PA448|year=1996|publisher=Wayne State University Press|isbn=0-8143-2353-7|page=448}}</ref><ref name="a">Hebrew Union College. ''[http://huc.edu/research/libraries/collections/ajpc-ij AMERICAN JEWISH PERIODICAL CENTER I-J]''</ref> The first issue was published on April 22, 1932, the last issue was published on May 2, 1952.<ref name="a"/> ''The Iowa Jewish News'' was published on Fridays.<ref name="b"/> Jack Wolfe was the editor of ''The Iowa Jewish News''.<ref name="b">{{cite book|title=Ayer Directory of Publications|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8gQjAQAAMAAJ|year=1955|publisher=Ayer Press|page=337}}</ref><ref name="c">{{cite book|author=Frank Rosenthal|title=The Jews of Des Moines: the first century|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zap5AAAAMAAJ|year=1957|publisher=Jewish Welfare Federation|page=92}}</ref> In its later period, the publication had a circulation of 1,817.<ref name="b"/>

